Description: McCortney Family In-home Care provides companionship and family home care services to seniors.
Full Description: McCortney Family In-home Care provides companionship and family home care services to seniors. Our caregivers serve aged adults recovering from surgery or a chronic illness, or simply needing assistance with daily chores to lead an independent life in the comfort of their familiar surroundings at home. Our clients also include new and expectant mothers, adults with special needs, families with cases of cognitive disorders like Alzheimers, Dementia, etc. We offer hourly up to 24 hour live-in care. In home care is one of the best options when it comes to older adults. Most often they do not have a medical condition that requires them to stay in a nursing home; however, they are unable to live completely on their own and take care of themselves. They need a hand with many aspects of daily life, be it housekeeping, meal preparation, personal hygiene, driving, or even companionship. Quite often, a family member helps to assist these senior members of the family. However, with time constraints and the demanding needs of elder care, it becomes challenging for most family members to shoulder the responsibility alone. This is especially true for older family members with a medical condition that needs special care. At this stage, in-home care is usually the best option.  It is a specialized service which is reliable, safe, and more importantly, provided in your home.  Your loved one does not have to leave his (or her) spouse, pets, and memories behind to live at an assisted living facility or nursing home.

Description: Healthcare
Full Description: MISSION - Our mission is to partner with physicians of different specialties to provide high quality services that are evidence-based and improve clinical outcomes. Our initial services are radiation oncology, and renal dialysis. VISION - Our vision is to be the first national clinical enterprise to consolidate ambulatory services from multiple specialties. RATIONALE - ASA was formed in response to powerful health care market trends: Consistent migration of services from the hospital to the outpatient setting Growing recognition that health care delivery is not uniform among providers, and that quality is variable Increasing patient demand for convenience without sacrificing quality Universal need among payers to control costs Physicians seek more control over the delivery of services as reimbursement for their services diminishes   The clinical rationale for ASA: Assists practices to develop information technology capability to enhance the practice of evidence-based medicine Permits practices to benchmark with peers and share best practices Helps practices adopt expensive new technologies and expand their service offerings Creates a national network of practices to facilitate clinical investigation, providing patients with access to novel therapies   The business rationale for ASA: Sharing information technology and other infrastructure among business units reduces operating costs Diversification of service lines reduces revenue risk from payers Consolidation of services strengthens lobbying position with Congress and centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) Facilitates national contracting for multiple service sites Joint-venture model aligns interests of ASA and physician partners to provide cost-effective and high quality services Creates an opportunity for physician partners and ASA associates to participate in the value created in the public equity market In concert with physician partners, ASA helps hospitals develop business strategies to provide ambulatory services The model attracts and retains a talented work force

Nutrition tracking and analytics platform for elite athletes and teams
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: NutriUnit is a nutrition tracking platform for elite athletes. We help athletes and teams monitor and meet their nutrition goals. NutriUnit is incorporating competition into nutrition thus tapping into the same drive that got athletes to the elite level of sports they are at. As young athletes move up in the world, many times they are faced with living on their own for the first time.  They are having to feed themselves for the first time, they have constantly changing class, practice and sleep schedules.  This is an extremely stressful time of change for many athletes.  NutriUnit is there to help bring regularity and accountability back into their lives and help them reach the goals they and their coaches have set for them. Almost every aspect of an athlete's training is down to a science; their lifting, their practices, cycling their intensity, as well as game preparation.  Competition is ingrained in all these areas. NutriUnit is extending that same competitive drive into your athletes' nutrition. By seeing their teammates progress throughout the day, they are constantly reminded of what they can do to stay competitive. The NutriUnit nutrition algorithm gives each athlete a custom nutrition goal which changes with their training intensity and whether they are in or out of season. NutriUnit was built by former collegiate athletes with one goal in mind, to make nutrition tracking accessible, affordable, and realistic for all levels of competitive sports.

Description: A podcast about mental health and addiction recovery.
Full Description: Stigma is the number 1 reason why people do not get help when they struggle with mental health issues, or addiction.  A lot of people who need help, never get help. When we share our stories and experiences, a virtuous cycle begins.  Others are encouraged to share their stories, and eventually, people hear these messages and feel comfortable asking for help. On this podcast, we will talk with entrepreneurs, leaders, founders, investors, doctors, and top performers about how mental health has impacted their lives.  We will learn from their experiences and listen when they tell us how they proactively manage their mental well-being. We believe that by encouraging increased conversation, we are fighting against stigma and encouraging others to not only share, but seek help when they need it.

Description: TOLIS Group is very proud that BRU™ technology was used to protect the irreplaceable and Saturn projects
Full Description: TOLIS Group, Inc., is a privately held profitable and debt-free corporation headquartered in Phoenix, Arizona. The singular focus of TOLIS Group™ is the development and support of ultra-reliable data backup, restore, and archival solutions for end-users and OEMs based on TOLIS Group's proven BRU™ technology. The genesis of BRU in 1985 as a commercially available tool was driven by the inability of popular tar-based operations to reliably backup and restore archives on Unix systems. The mandate of BRU's design was to return the most data possible during a restore, limited only by physical damage. In January of 2005 TOLIS Group announced its bruAPP™ Backup Appliance solution.   bruAPP™ is a data backup and restore-focused appliance that delivers the industry's first truly "server-less" backup services across client/server system topologies. The bruAPP™ Backup Appliance virtually eliminates the configuration, installation, and compatibility issues faced when designing and building a data backup system. In January of 2010, TOLIS Group entered further into the hardware market providing one stop shopping and support for tape and BRU software bundled offerings. In 2018 TOLIS Group will enter the Windows market with BRU Producer's Edition™ for Windows, and enhanced offerings to it's bruAPP™ Backup Appliance for the Windows user.
